'''Max Chilton''' (born [[April 21]], [[1991]]) is an [[England|English]] racing driver who currently races for [[Hitech Racing]] in the [[British Formula Three Championship]]. He is currently a student at [[Ardingly College]], [[West Sussex]]. His brother [[Tom Chilton|Tom]] is also a racing driver, currently competing in the [[British Touring Car Championship]].

Max made his debut at the second round of the [[2007 British Formula Three season]], as he was below the required age of 16 to take part in the season opener. With initial success in this series, he hopes to replicate the success of fellow Brit [[Lewis Hamilton]], and drive in [[Formula 1]].<ref>{{cite web | author=Hayes, Chris | title=Chilton, the next Lewis Hamilton? | work=Forumula1.net | url=http://www.forumula1.net/2008/f1/f1-news/exclusive-chilton-the-next-lewis-hamilton/ | accessdate=2008-05-19}}</ref>

